```
git log --all --grep "RELEASE"
```

Displays nothing but it should be in sync with our git.bioconductor.org repository and have the commits from last release.

Something like
```
Author: Nitesh Turaga <nitesh.turaga at gmail.com>
Date:   Thu May 2 12:14:38 2019 -0400

    bump x.y.z versions to odd y after creation of RELEASE_3_9    branch

```

